The factors that contributed to the Ottoman Empire's entry into World War I as a Central Power were:

* The agreement formed by Ottoman leaders to form an alliance with Germany against Russia on July 30, 1914, which did not require them to undertake military action;
* The combined German-Ottoman surprise attack on the Black Sea coast of the Russian Empire on October 29, 1914;
* The subsequent declarations of war by Russia (November 2, 1914), France (November 5, 1914), and Britain (November 5, 1914) against the Ottoman Empire.
